gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nets 112, 76ers 107
gameRecap.excerpt: The Nets defeated the Sixers, 112-107 as they outscored Philadelphia 32-24 in the final quarter. Dorian Finney-Smith (20 points, eight rebounds) and Dennis Schroder (20 points, eight assists) led five Brooklyn players in doubles as Nic Claxton added 17 points, 10 rebounds, and four blocks. Kelly Oubre Jr. led the Sixers with 30 points, six rebounds, and four assists. Brooklyn improves to 25-37 on the year as the Sixers move to 35-26, as the loss snaps a two-game win streak.
